  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nThe public endpoint now limits the block range of the event queries so when using the watcher service the endpoint will return with `eth_getLogs are limited to a 10,000 blocks range` error. But there's currently no way to set the `startingBlock` in the watcher service as `NUM_BLOCKS_TO_FETCH` is hardcoded atm.\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e23b26430b7252057abc800a134d8484af14f917/packages/core-utils/src/watcher.ts#L86\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/e23b26430b7252057abc800a134d8484af14f917/packages/core-utils/src/watcher.ts#L20\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n1. Add a note in the doc to inform developers that they should run their own node when using watcher service.\r\n2. Allow passing in the `startingBlock` param of the event query or configuring `NUM_BLOCKS_TO_FETCH ` in watcher service\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nThread on Discord: https://discord.com/channels/667044843901681675/676980316518481930/879581524373172274",
